reviews.review_text: One for the ages In my humble opinion this was one AMAZING show. I saw 400+ shows from 8/7/82>8/4/94 (I was a bit of a fanatic 😜) and two shows from 1984 always seems to ring true in my mind as being top shows. 10/12/84 Augusta & this one 6/30/84. Yes the set lists were cool but that's not it. Both these shows had that indescribable "IT" that magic. Happily that "magic" mostly, does transfer on audio tape. I remember no backdrop, u could see the equipment truck pulled up to the stage. It was a small venue, tennis courts or something. They never went back as Deer Creek became the venue in those parts. Highlights Lost>Saint>Dead. Killer pre-drums Shakedown>Playing>Terrapin. A very rare Bobby lead guitar solo on "Spoonful". One of those shows I know instantly when I hear it. Right from opening notes. Similar to the incomparable CRS from 10/12/84. I know its THAT CRS opening note
